[ in husk — juicier, recommended for supermarket corn ]
- soak ears in water for 10-15 mins
- bbq to medium-high
- place on grates as-is, turn every 5 mins for 20-25 mins
- husk should be well charred
- peel back husk and silks, finish direct on grates for 1-2 mins for colour
- butter and salt to serve

[ husked — more char, more caramelisation ]
- peel husk and silks off
- brush with oil or butter, salt
- bbq to medium-high
- place direct on grates, turn every 2-3 mins for 10 mins total
- butter and season to serve

in-husk is better for supermarket corn (older, drier) — steams in its own moisture and stays juicy
husked is better for very fresh corn where you want caramelisation on the kernels
